    <main>
      <section id="MusicPortfolio" class="relative">
        <div class="container1000">
          <h2>music portfolio</h2>
          <iframe
            width="100%"
            height="600"
            height="600"
            scrolling="no"
            frameborder="no"
            src="https://play.reelcrafter.com/embed/424662f2-4458-484d-b304-f608f2e839eb"
            class="song-player"
          >
          </iframe>
        </div>
      </section>
      <section id="Credits">
        <div class="container1000">
          <h2>credits</h2>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 grid-cols-1 gap-4">
            <div class="flex flex-col justify-start items-center">
              <h4>The lonely body - 2023</h4>
              <a
                href={lonelyBodyUrl}
                class="cursor-pointer transition ease-in-out delay-100 hover:opacity-80 hover:scale-105 shadow-image"
              >
                <Image src={TheLonelyBody} alt="The lonely body" height="500" />
              </a>
              <div
                class="flex flex-col justify-between py-8 px-4 md:p-8 h-full"
              >
                <p class="italic">
                  "Nina delivered a hauntingly brilliant score for The Lonely
                  Body. She had an intuitive grasp of the material from the
                  outset and was a joy to collaborate with leaving us with a
                  score that far exceeded my expectations. I look forward to
                  working with her again on my next film."
                </p>

                <a
                  href="https://www.imdb.com/name/nm13635190/"
                  class="flex justify-start items-center mt-8 mb-16 cursor-pointer group"
                >
                  <Image
                    src={TimBrown}
                    width="80"
                    height="80"
                    alt="Tim Brown"
                    class="rounded-full mr-4"
                  />
                  <span class="group-hover:underline transition-all ease-in-out"
                    >Tim Brown / Director</span
                  ></a
                >
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex flex-col justify-start items-center">
              <h4>La luce di Roma - 2021</h4>
              <a
                href={luceDiRomaUrl}
                class="cursor-pointer transition ease-in-out delay-100 hover:opacity-80 hover:scale-105 shadow-image"
              >
                <Image src={LaLuceDiRoma} alt="La luce di Roma" height="500" />
              </a>
              <div
                class="flex flex-col justify-between py-8 px-4 md:p-8 h-full"
              >
                <p class="italic">
                  "I chose Nina Madison's music because her melodies perfectly
                  captured the spirit of our documentary. It's as if Nina,
                  despite not fully knowing our narrative intentions, knew from
                  the beginning where we wanted to take our audience and helped
                  us achieve this with excellence. I find her music to be very
                  evocative and persuasive, pulling at your heartstrings at the
                  right moment.”
                </p>
                <a
                  href="https://guidotalarico.com/"
                  class="flex justify-start items-center mt-8 mb-16 cursor-pointer group"
                >
                  <Image
                    src={GuidoTalarico}
                    width="80"
                    height="80"
                    alt="Guido Talarico"
                    class="rounded-full mr-4"
                  />
                  <span class="group-hover:underline transition-all ease-in-out"
                    >Guido Talarico / Director</span
                  >
                </a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="UpcomingProjects" class="bg-white text-notexactlyblack">
        <div class="container1000 !py-40">
          <h2 class="text-notexactlyblack">upcoming projects</h2>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 grid-cols-1 gap-8">
            <div class="flex flex-col h-full justify-between">
              <h4 class="text-left text-notexactlyblack">
                Eternal Seas <br />
                <a
                  class="text-accent underline font-bold hover:text-notexactlyblack transition-all ease-in-out"
                  href="https://store.steampowered.com/app/2124010/Eternal_Seas/"
                  >Versnel Studios</a
                >
              </h4>
              <p>
                Eternal Seas is an open world pirate RPG inspired by classic
                pirate games, set in a fictional island region. Command mighty
                vessels and lead your crew across the high seas and through lush
                jungles. Will you find fortune or will your soul be damned to
                sail the seas eternally?
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex flex-col h-full justify-between">
              <h4 class="text-left text-notexactlyblack">
                'Spazio Vuoto' (Short, 2023/2024) <br />
                <a
                  class="text-accent underline font-bold hover:text-notexactlyblack transition-all ease-in-out"
                  href="https://www.instagram.com/brandolino_brandolini/"
                  >Brandolino Brandolini D'Adda</a
                > and <a
                  class="text-accent underline font-bold hover:text-notexactlyblack transition-all ease-in-out"
                  href="https://www.instagram.com/cosimo_desii/">Cosimo Desii</a
                >
              </h4>
              <p>
                Spazio Vuoto delves into the story of a young man returning home
                after his father's death. On this journey of self-discovery, he
                must confront the neglected relationship he had with his father
                and the memories of the home he grew up in, to finally move
                forward and live a life unburdened by the past.
              </p>
            </div>
